<br>
Pet DO push, like player push, like mob push... The key is you need to have pet classes with a brain and melee that trust the pet classes to take the right decision and position their pets well. Heck in my guild, we don't blame pet for pushing, we use them to push. =p<br>
<br>
Personnally I'm pretty much the decision maker as far as using pets is concerned in my guild. And as long as you have pet hold and at least 2 or 3 brain cells, you can use pet all the time everywhere as far as I'm concerned. People without pet hold or with pets that can't be controlled are another thing though. Same goes with pet swarms, those have a lot more restriction as to when and how you can use them. But the person that can prove me it's better for me not to use pet isn't born yet on my server. ;p And I've been using pet all the time pretty much since this game opened. If I was able to use a pet without screwing up in plane of hate at lvl 50 when pets were not neutral, could break mez and pet hold didn't exist, I damn sure will be able to use a pet all the damn time now with those abilities.<br>
<br>
Pet control used to be a thing I took pride in doing well, I had to fight for the right to use pets and at the beginning if I had made any mistake I would have got my ass kicked (I wasn't an officer back then, I was a simple little mage fighting for his right to use a pet). But after seeing a few hate raids where pet didn't break mez, didn't run off, didn't attack wrong target, etc, I finally won my point and haven't been bothered much about it since. And the few that tried got turned around pretty fast. =p<br>
<br>
It all boils down to 1) guildies trusting the pet classes 2) pet classes using their brain when sending pet in and 3) a little bitching at the start to prove your point. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
