<br>
Anyway, if your MT doesn't like pet push, than he's mentally deficient. I can think of like 4 encounters in the game where the mob isn't pinned in one spot, and of those pins, most are pinned with face to wall, ass to room anyway.  And, if you need to pin a mob in a stationary place, pets are even better, because they don't complain about being positioned at the front. They'll happily wack away at the front and keep the mob in a single place, so that players can be at the sides and the back.<br>
<br>
